<P>
 UNDER THE BLACK FLAG by Erik Christian Haugaard (Roberts Rinehart: $8.95; 163 
pp., paperback original). An award-winning juvenile author, Erik Haugaard 
presents the adventures of William Bernard, a teen-ager traveling to England 
from his father's plantation in Jamaica, who is kidnaped by the infamous 
Blackbeard. Although he spins an exciting yarn, Haugaard never glamorizes the 
pirates. As Blackbeard's de facto cabin boy, William has ample opportunity to 
observe their cruelty and the miserable conditions aboard a 17th-Century 
sailing ship. Informative but never didactic, "Flag" will claim the attention 
of any young readers. 
</P>
