<TEXT>
<P>
 THE INDEX OF LEADING CULTURAL INDICATORS: Facts and Figures on the State of 
American Society by William J. Bennett (Touchstone: $8.95; 138 pp., paperback 
original). Figures may not lie, but they can be juggled, and William Bennett 
handles statistics as skillfully as a performer on the Venice boardwalk.He 
cites the high rates of abortion and teen-age pregnancy in America, but fails 
to correlate those figures with a dearth of family planning information. He 
claims, "Armed citizens defend their lives or property with firearms against 
criminals approximately 1 million times a year," but omits the number of 
murders committed by family members in gun-owning households. Bennett sets the 
tone for this sermon to the choir when he decries the failure of Americans to 
provide moral education for the young -- ignoring the examples set by the 
amoral policies of the administrations he served. 
</P>
