<P>
 LOVERS' CHOICE by Becky Birtha (Seal Press: $10.95; 152 pp.). Although many of 
Birtha's stories involve lesbians dealing with questions of commitment, her 
most effective writing probes the complex feelings African American women share 
with their female relatives.In "Baby Town," a little girl accompanies her 
mother, aunt and sister to a cemetery and experiences the first chilling 
intimations of her own mortality; "Johnnieruth" captures the impatience of an 
adolescent girl eager to explore the possibilities that lie beyond the familiar 
blocks where her mother insists she remain. 
