<HEADLINE>
<P>
BERNARDI AND CRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * In response to "Turning the Tables: CRA Buys Star on Walk of Fame for 
Longtime Critic," Feb. 26: 
</P>
<P>
 Perhaps former City Councilman Ernani Bernardi's Walk of Fame star will shine 
bright on those Community Redevelopment Agency officials responsible for this 
"gotcha," and expose them for what they really are. For 32 years, he has been 
fighting these outlaws who are so articulate in redefining blight they have 
been able to sell their glamorous developments to the public without being 
accountable in any way. 
</P>
<P>
 Using tax dollars to purchase a star is but a hint of their irresponsible 
waste. Bernardi obviously recognizes this is being done by confiscating 
millions upon millions of hard-earned tax dollars from other desperately needed 
services, such as police and fire protection, and schools. Most people are not 
aware that redevelopment agencies do not answer to the voters or their elected 
representatives, that they are an administrative arm of the state, and they can 
create debt in inconceivable amounts that eventually must be paid from the 
income of the citizens. 
</P>
<P>
 Bernardi does know. Hopefully his star will shed some light so others can 
observe the horrors fathered by this much maligned and misunderstood back room 
of our government. 
</P>
<P>
 BOB SLAGLE 
</P>
<P>
 Big Bear Lake 
</P>
