<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIREFIGHTER EXAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I am appalled that Los Angeles is barring white males from its firefighter 
examination. We need our firefighters to be the best qualified individuals 
available.A firefighter today needs to be able to understand the treatment of 
hazardous materials. They need to be able to do the complex hydrodynamic 
calculations to determine how many, and what sizes of hose lines can be 
supported. And of course, a firefighter still needs the strength to carry a 
victim (possibly another firefighter) out of a hazardous area. 
</P>
<P>
 I, for one, don't care whether a firefighter is male, female, black, yellow, 
brown, green, or even white. That doesn't matter. What matters is having the 
best qualified individuals available in times of emergency. Barring 5,000 
individuals from taking the examination is ensuring that our new firefighters 
will not be the most qualified individuals as our firefighters. This is neither 
equal opportunity nor fair to the public. 
</P>
