and Girl Scouts, not the reverse. The Times calls for a drop in litigation by 
(the Boy Scouts) ("Business of Scouting," Editorial, March 2), not to defend 
their values that are being attacked. 
</P>
<P>
 The Times is wrong. It is the Randalls who should drop their attack on (the 
Boy Scouts and Girl Scouts), gather all of the atheists, form their own 
organization, and go their own way, and take The Times with them. 
