<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNBEATEN BREA-OLINDA WINS DIVISION III-AA TITLE, 70-40 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda, three-time defending state girls' champion and top-ranked by The 
Times, lived up to expectations with a 70-40 victory over No. 17 Newport Harbor 
in the Southern Section Division III-AA championship at Cal Poly Pomona on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Before about 2,000, Sarah Beckley led the Ladycats (29-0) with 18 points and 
12 rebounds.Colleen Hudson and Nicole Erickson added 15 each. 
</P>
<P>
 Genevieve Evarts led Newport Harbor (22-7) with 22 points. 
</P>
<P>
 The title was the first for Coach John Hattrup, who replaced Mark Trakh, and 
was Brea's sixth in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our kids have been here before and we know what these games are like," 
Hattrup said. "If we have a good game plan and play hard, we know good things 
will happen." MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
