<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDNER LEADS ST. JOHN BOSCO PAST DOMINGUEZ FOR II-A TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARRY BAUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jelani Gardner, a 6-foot-6 senior point guard, scored 12 of his 24 points in 
the fourth quarter to carry No. 6-ranked Bellflower St. John Bosco to a 55-54 
victory over No. 3 Compton Dominguez High in the Southern Section Division II-A 
championship at Anaheim Arena on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 "We tried to throw everything at him we could and get the ball out of his 
hands," said Dominguez Coach Russell Otis. 
</P>
<P>
 Leading 53-51, St. John Bosco (28-2) got possession after a steal by Gardner 
with 24 seconds left. Gardner was fouled with 10 seconds to play, and he hit 
two free throws to culminate a 7-0 run that made it 55-51. Jaimie Gillin of 
Dominguez hit a three-pointer at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
 Their 17th consecutive victory gave the Braves their first section title. The 
loss ended a 17-game winning streak by Dominguez (27-3), which has now lost two 
title games in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons hit two of six free throws; the Braves 11 of 15. BARRY BAUM 
</P>
</TEXT>
