<HEADLINE>
<P>
A BITTERSWEET DISH ON DUTCH MENU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Dutch restaurant is turning the culinary clock back to the time of the Nazi 
occupation by serving tulip bulb soup. 
</P>
<P>
 Chef Rob Pauv at the Igesz restaurant in this northwestern city is keeping the 
recipe under his hat, but he said Friday that employees at the restaurant who 
have tasted the dish say it's delicious. 
</P>
<P>
 During the "Hunger Winter" of 1944, the German occupiers stripped the nation 
of foodstuffs to send to Germany. 
</P>
<P>
 The starving Dutch dug up and cooked bitter tulip bulbs from their gardens to 
stay alive. 
</P>
