<P>
CENSUS WORKERS PLAN IN-DEPTH LOOK AT AMERICA'S HOMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Census Bureau workers will fan out in eight metropolitan areas later this 
month to take the agency's 21st annual in-depth look at America's homes. 
</P>
<P>
 Census workers will visit about 4,700 homes in each of eight metropolitan 
areas: Buffalo, N.Y.; Milwaukee; Dallas; Ft. Worth; Phoenix; Anaheim-Santa Ana; 
Riverside-San Bernardino, and San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 The survey is conducted for the Department of Housing and Urban Development, 
which uses the information in studies of housing in central cities and suburban 
areas. 
