<HEADLINE>
<P>
7 PEASANTS KILLED IN MEXICO AMBUSH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seven people were killed and at least one was injured in an ambush in southern 
Mexico, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The dead and injured were among 20 men, women and children traveling by truck 
Friday on a highway near the rural community of San Nicolas Yaxe, the 
government of Oaxaca state said. 
</P>
<P>
 The truck was intercepted by 15 gunmen who forced some occupants to get out 
and then fired on the people still inside with high-powered weapons, the 
state-owned news agency Notimex reported. 
</P>
<P>
 San Nicolas Yaxe and nearby San Baltazar Chichicapam have been involved in a 
longstanding conflict over land. In 1986, the conflict led to several clashes 
between peasants from the two communities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
