<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: CLOUDY SKIES TO LINGER, LIGHT SHOWERS POSSIBLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County residents can expect cloudy skies again today and a chance of 
light showers, the National Weather Service said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 There is also a possibility of thunderstorms as warm air from the eastern 
Pacific mixes with a cold front from the Gulf of Alaska, said Stuart Seto of 
the National Weather Service in Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 The storm system probably will pass through the area by this afternoon, and 
clear skies will return to the county on Monday, with highs reaching the 70s, 
Seto said. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
