<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; CAMARILLO CONTINUES SLUGGING IN WESTSIDE TOURNAMENT WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert Smith drove in four runs with two triples to lead Camarillo High to a 
15-6 victory over University on Saturday in a Westside tournament game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Scorpions, who have scored 36 runs in two games, had 11 hits. Nathan Kaup 
had two hits, three runs batted in and three runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting pitcher Aaron Hanel (1-0) had five strikeouts and no walks in five 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Westside tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth 8, Ventura 1 -- Ray Daryabigi (1-0) pitched a four-hitter and went 
three for four with two stolen bases for the Chancellors. Mike Amato, Tony 
Montiel (two RBIs) and Brandon Murphy each had two hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Rio Mesa 5, Westchester 2 -- Junior left-hander Richard Soliz allowed no 
earned runs in a four-hitter for Rio Mesa (1-1). Albert Ambriz's double and 
Donald DiDomizio's sacrifice fly in the second inning gave the Spartans a 3-0 
lead. Eric Flores went two for three with two stolen bases. 
</P>
<P>
 Montclair Prep 16, Culver City 6 -- Montclair Prep scored 15 runs in the final 
two innings. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mounties trailed, 6-1, in the sixth when they erupted for nine runs with 
two out. Darrell Dent stole home while Culver City's catcher went to the mound 
without calling time out. 
</P>
<P>
 Montclair Prep (2-0) added six more runs in the seventh. Sophomore catcher 
Andrew Miller went three for five with four RBIs and Matt Muler also had four 
RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus 8 Santa Monica 1 -- Six players each had two hits for the Centurions 
(2-0) and Steve Rogers pitched five solid innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Hueneme 4, Palisades 3 -- Raudel Flores scored the winning run on a 
bases-loaded single by Art Bolen (three for four) in the bottom of the seventh 
for Hueneme (1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Chaminade 10, Taft 2 -- Kevin Lohman's triple with the bases loaded 
highlighted a five-run fourth inning for Chaminade. Chaminade (1-1) got solid 
pitching from Gabe Crecion and Casey Cote, allowing the Toreadors (1-1) three 
hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Crecion, Scot Dey and Adam Crecion each had two hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame 10, Canyon 2 -- Rich Igou's three-run home run in the fifth lifted 
Notre Dame. Freshman Juan Montes pitched three innings for the save, striking 
out four. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart 1, Channel Islands 0 -- Luis Sanchez outdueled Channel Islands' Rene 
Sanchez. Hart (2-0) scored in the fifth inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Crossroads 9, Oxnard 7 -- Oxnard got run-scoring singles from Eric Terrill, 
Chuck Harrington and Ernie Hernandez in a five-run first inning before 
Crossroads got even. 
</P>
