<P>
HELP WITH CREDIT, FINANCES ON TAP AT 5TH HOME FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Do you have credit problems? Are you short on cash for a down payment? Do you 
need to refinance but have no equity? Do you qualify for special mortgage 
assistance? 
</P>
<P>
 If these are your questions, bring them to the fifth annual Times' Home Buyers 
and Sellers Fair, 9:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. on Saturday, March 19, at the Anaheim 
Convention Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The one-day consumer education event will offer a workshop on credit problems 
and how to solve them. Also on hand will be the Consumer Credit Counseling 
Service, a nonprofit agency that advises homeowners and buyers on their 
individual problems. 
</P>
<P>
 For those interested in refinancing but worried about their equity or ability 
to qualify, a special workshop will be held in conjunction with Mortgage 
Originator Magazine. 
</P>
<P>
 A special "Paths to Homeownership" exhibit area, sponsored with Fannie Mae, 
will include representatives of government agencies such as the City of Los 
Angeles Housing Department, California Housing Finance Agency, FHA, VA and the 
California Department of Veterans Affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 Home-buying panels will be conducted in three languages: English, Spanish and 
Mandarin Chinese. For details, please see ad on Page K4. 
</P>
