<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAN NEW PERSHING SQUARE PREVAIL?; DESTROYED CONDOS MAY NOT BE REPAIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This letter concerns condominiums that were destroyed or substantially damaged 
by the Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Your readers who own condos need to know that California law does not require 
that destroyed units be repaired. Section 1364 (a) of the California Civil Code 
states that the owners' association is responsible for repairing, replacing or 
maintaining the common areas, unless otherwise provided in the declaration of 
the development. It is not unusual for such declarations to allow the owners to 
decide whether destroyed units will be repaired. Concerned readers should 
carefully review their declarations to determine their rights and the time 
period in which their rights may be exercised. 
</P>
<P>
 J. ANTHONY MARINO 
</P>
<P>
 Encino 
</P>
<P>
 The writer is an attorney.  
</P>
</TEXT>
