</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The American Diabetes Assn.'s Latino Programs Committee has scheduled a free 
class on foot complications associated with the chronic disease and free foot 
exams from 9 a.m. to noon Saturday at USC University Hospital, 1500 San Pablo 
St. 
</P>
<P>
 Podiatrist Michael Vega will talk about the importance of proper foot care.  
</P>
<P>
 The Spanish-language program will include a question-and-answer period. 
</P>
<P>
 Diabetes impairs the body's ability to convert sugar into energy and requires 
lifestyle changes for proper management and control. 
</P>
<P>
 If left untreated, it can lead to blindness, amputation, heart attack and 
stroke. 
</P>
