<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: BELL GARDENS; COUNCILMAN GARCIA FINED $1,500 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY HELEN BERG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The state Fair Political Practices Commission has fined Councilman Rodolfo 
(Rudy) Garcia $1,500 for violating state conflict-of-interest laws when he 
voted to fire City Manager William Vasquez last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia approached Vasquez in July, 1992, and, citing personal financial 
difficulties, asked Vasquez for a $1,000 loan, according to a commission 
report.Vasquez complied, giving Garcia the loan in cash. There was no written 
agreement. 
</P>
<P>
 Eight months later, Garcia cast a key vote in a 3-2 city council decision to 
dismiss Vasquez. State law prohibits public officials from voting on matters 
involving people with whom they have loans. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia also failed to list Vasquez as a source of income on 1992 economic 
disclosure forms but later amended the financial statements, the report said. 
</P>
<P>
 Because Garcia was cooperative and candid with the commission and had no 
history of violations, the commission did not fine him the maximum penalty of 
$2,000, a commission spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia said he had no idea his action was improper. He could not be reached 
for comment Friday. MARY HELEN BERG 
</P>
</TEXT>
