<HEADLINE>
<P>
WRESTLING; BELL HIGH WRESTLERS REPEAT CITY SECTION CHAMPION FEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SMITH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Bell High School wrestling team edged out the visiting squad from El 
Camino Real to repeat as City Section champs. 
</P>
<P>
 "We take a lot of pride in winning back-to-back championships because we 
haven't been around for very long," Bell Coach Frank O'Connor said of the 
school's 4-year-old program."The Valley schools wanted to win the title back 
but we wanted to keep it in the city, and we did." 
</P>
<P>
 Of the seven wrestlers the Eagles placed in the Feb. 26 finals at Bell, Jose 
Gonzales (112-pound class), Ramses Ochoa (145), Frank Ordorica (171), Jesus 
Orozco (189) and Adolfo Padilla (heavyweight) won in their respective weight 
classes. 
</P>
<P>
 Orozco, whose victory in the City championship had been preceded twice by 
losses, was voted outstanding wrestler of the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzales' victory marked his third championship in as many years. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzales, Ochoa, Ordorica, Orozco and Padilla advanced to this weekend's State 
championship at the University of the Pacific in Stockton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
