<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WINE LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dan Berger 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It may not be a trend yet, but Clearwater Cafe has the first wine list I have 
seen with a section devoted to wines made from organically farmed grapes, which 
are grown without pesticides, fungicides or chemical fertilizers. The five-wine 
category includes the two widest-selling organic wines from Fetzer Vineyards. 
</P>
<P>
 There is a changing list of micro-brewed beers on tap. Recently, it included 
Big Rock XO Lager and Royal Coachman Dry Ale, both from Canada; Oregon Honey 
Beer and Widmer Hefeweizen, an unfiltered wheat beer, both from Portland; St. 
Rogue Red, a hearty brew from Newport, Ore., and Grant's Scottish Ale from 
Yakima, Wash. All brews may be ordered by the pint or 12-ounce glass.  
</P>
<P>
 The all-West Coast wine list, heavy on the whites because of the seafood 
emphasis, has a number of good values, including 1991 Benziger Fume Blanc, $19; 
1992 Frog's Leap Sauvignon, $18; 1991 Navarro Gewurztraminer, $18, and 1991 
Chateau St. Jean Chardonnay, $19. Dan Berger 
</P>
</TEXT>
