<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN IN CRITICAL CONDITION AFTER SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 18-year-old man was in critical condition Saturday after he was shot during 
an argument that erupted at a Sylmar residence, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles police arrested a 25-year-old Los Angeles man on suspicion of 
attempted murder.Authorities refused to name the alleged shooter. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, Randy Cooper, also of Los Angeles, was taken to Holy Cross Medical 
Center in Mission Hills after the 9:40 p.m. shooting Friday.  
</P>
<P>
 Cooper and the suspect were among a group of young men and women who had 
gathered at a residence in the 14100 block of Foothill Boulevard, Lt. Joseph 
Garcia of the LAPD's Foothill Division said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cooper was shot in the upper body after he and the suspect argued. Police said 
they do not know why the two argued. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect was arrested at the scene and the gun used in the shooting was 
recovered, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA030694-0280 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 020198 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
