115 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; ARTS: TEMPLE TO DEDICATE STAINED-GLASS WINDOWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Sephardic Temple Tifereth Israel in Los Angeles has installed 
stained-glass "Sephardic Heritage Windows" designed by Israeli artist Raphael 
Abecassis. 
</P>
<P>
 The windows, commissioned by the Maurice Amado Foundation, will be dedicated 
at 11 a.m. March 13. They will serve as a living memorial to longtime temple 
members Dr. Morris and Regina Tarica. 
</P>
<P>
 Abecassis used Jewish symbols, Sephardic motifs and modern composition to 
complete the 22-foot-high windows, which include 6,000 separate pieces of 
glass. 
</P>
<P>
 The windows depict the history of Sephardic Jews, beginning with their 
expulsion from Spain in the 15th Century. 
</P>
<P>
 The temple, at 10500 Wilshire Blvd., is open to the public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
