<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOCCER / CITY SECTION CHAMPIONSHIPS; BELMONT AND GRANT GRAB TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ENRIQUE LAVIN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Belmont High upset top-seeded Bell, 1-0, in the boys' City Section soccer 
final Saturday, and Van Nuys Grant beat San Pedro by the same score to become 
the second team to win the girls' championship. 
</P>
<P>
 Ana Hufanga of Grant and Jose Salmeron of Belmont had second-half goals to 
provide all the scoring for the 300 spectators who watched the doubleheader at 
Birmingham High in Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 Hufanga's goal came four minutes into the second half after Nicole Bucciarelli 
drove the ball to the top of the San Pedro goal box and passed it to Hufanga. 
Hufanga made a fake and blasted it home for the Lancers' first championship in 
three appearances. They finished 12-3-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Salmeron, a striker, scored his 14th goal of the season at the 60-minute mark 
after receiving a throw-in pass from Nelson Moran. Salmeron's goal was only the 
10th given up by the Eagles all season. 
</P>
<P>
 "The way we started the season, we would have never believed we were going to 
be here," said Belmont Coach Nancy Carr-Swaim, who guided the Sentinels 
(10-1-2) to the 1992 final, but lost to Garfield, 2-1. "This is the most 
well-rounded team that I've ever coached." 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles outshot the Sentinels, 12-8, forcing Belmont goalies Octavio 
Calvillo and Mario Orellana to make three key saves each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
