<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEHERE SCHEDULED TO HAVE SURGERY ON HIS BROKEN LEG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Surgery is planned Tuesday for 2-year-old champion Dehere, who suffered a 
broken right hind leg in a workout Friday and won't run in any of the Triple 
Crown races. 
</P>
<P>
 Dehere is "receiving medication and is resting as well as can be expected," 
trainer Reynaldo Nobles said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Dehere was injured at Palm Beach Downs, a training center where the colt is 
wintering. Surgery is scheduled at a clinic in nearby Pompano Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 "We don't want him to have to travel too far and risk further damage," Nobles 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dehere was the early favorite for the Florida Derby on March 12. He beat 
favored and previously unbeaten Holy Bull and highly regarded Go For Gin in the 
$200,000 Fountain of Youth on Feb. 19. 
</P>
</TEXT>
