BRIEFLY; RESEARCH: NEW GROUP FOUNDED TO FIGHT DIABETES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Attorney Andrew Katzenstein of Santa Monica has founded Cure Diabetes Now, a 
nonprofit organization supporting diabetes research. 
</P>
<P>
 Katzenstein, who will be president, says the organization will focus on 
research aimed at finding a cure for diabetes rather than on educational or 
diagnostic work. 
</P>
<P>
 "Diabetes researchers are doing wonderful things, but many are dealing with 
the peripheral effects of the disease rather than the disease itself," he said. 
"We have one purpose only: to find a cure." 
</P>
