<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; WRIGHT THROWS NO-HITTER, HITS TWO HOMERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jaret Wright threw a no-hitter to lead Katella to a 7-1 victory over Laguna 
Hills in the second round of the Loara Diamond baseball tournament. Wright, who 
struck out 11 and walked only two, also had two home runs and four runs batted 
in for the Knights. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Loara Diamond tournament second-round championship bracket games: 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 6, Long Beach Jordan 1 -- Bryan Robinson had a perfect game 
through 6 1/3 innings and settled for the one-hitter. 
</P>
<P>
 Diamond Bar 4, Dana Hills 2 -- Johnny Schmidt's two-run home run in the sixth 
gave Diamond Bar (2-0) the lead. Dana Hills' Chris Toomey also hit a two-run 
homer. 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado 14, Newbury Park 6 -- Jeff Moore had two doubles, and Chris Beck had 
three singles for El Dorado (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 4, Kennedy 3 -- Luke Fox's single tied the score, and Kevin 
Burford's fielder's choice won it for Fountain Valley (2-0) in a three-run 
fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 6, Villa Park 5 -- Winning pitcher Eric Sobek (1-0) was also three for 
four with a two-run triple in the first inning for Irvine (2-0). 
</P>
