<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BASKETBALL CHAMPIONSHIPS; BELLFLOWER ST. JOHN BOSCO WINS II-A 
TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARRY BAUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jelani Gardner, a 6-foot-6 senior point guard, scored 12 of his 24 points in 
the fourth quarter to carry No. 6-ranked Bellflower St. John Bosco to a 55-54 
victory over No. 3 Compton Dominguez High in the Southern Section Division II-A 
championship Saturday at Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 "We tried to throw everything at him we could and get the ball out of his 
hands," Dominguez Coach Russell Otis said. 
</P>
<P>
 Leading 53-51, St. John Bosco (28-2) got possession after a steal by Gardner 
with 24 seconds left. Gardner was fouled with 10 seconds to play, and he hit 
two free throws to culminate a 7-0 run that made it 55-51. Jaimie Gillin of 
Dominguez hit a three-pointer at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
 Their 17th consecutive victory gave the Braves their first section title. The 
loss ended a 17-game winning streak by Dominguez (27-3), which has now lost two 
title games in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons hit two of six free throws; the Braves 11 of 15. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division I-AA boys' game: 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach Poly 71, La Crescenta Crescenta Valley 60 -- The Jackrabbits (25-6) 
outscored Crescenta Valley, 30-13, in the third quarter to cruise to their 14th 
section title, at the Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division II-AA boys' game: 
</P>
<P>
 Inglewood 77, No. 5 Riverside North 59 -- Paul Pierce scored 22 points, 
including the first seven points of the game to give the Sentinels (28-3) a 
lead they never relinquished, at the Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division V-AA boys' game: 
</P>
<P>
 North Hollywood Campbell Hall 46, Pasadena Poly 43 -- Alex Lopez scored 19 
points and had six blocked shots at Pepperdine as Campbell Hall (21-8) won for 
the second time in three years. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division I-AA girls' game: 
</P>
<P>
 Lynwood 53, Palos Verdes Peninsula 46 -- Tawana Grimes scored five consecutive 
points in the final two minutes to spark Lynwood (29-1), which had blown a 
15-point lead to trail by one point. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division II-A girls' game: 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Hills Alemany 59, San Bernardino 46 -- Alemany remained unbeaten in 28 
games, but had to weather a 26-point second-half outburst by San Bernardino's 
LaTonya Kindle, at Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division V-A girls' game: 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos Valley Christian 79, Sun Valley Village Christian 64 -- Lady Crusader 
center Jodi Parriott scored a game-high 45 points to lead Valley Christian. 
BARRY BAUM 
</P>
</TEXT>
