<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE MEN'S BASKETBALL; SADDLEBACK SLOWS DOWN IN LATE GOING, FALLS, 
72-66 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback, which had several chances in the final minute, failed to convert 
any of them and lost to host Long Beach, 72-66, Saturday in a men's basketball 
regional final. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach (29-6) advanced to the State tournament, which starts Thursday at 
UC Irvine. The loss marks the third consecutive season Saddleback has been 
beaten in a regional final. The Gauchos end their season, 23-9. 
</P>
<P>
 Tes Whitlock made two free throws with 1 minute 31 seconds left to cut Long 
Beach's lead to 69-66, but Saddleback never scored again. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach's Marc Neal and Kevin Beal then missed shots and Saddleback's 
Antoine Jefferson got the rebound with 57 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 After a timeout, Derrick Walsh drove to the basket but had the ball stripped 
by Long Beach's Marcus Woods with 45 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Still, Saddleback had a chance when Long Beach's Robert Darville missed the 
front end of a one-on-one with 27 seconds left. But Long Beach's Woods, the 
shortest player on the court, got the long rebound, allowing the Vikings to 
retain possession. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback fouled Beal with 18 seconds left and he made the first free throw 
to put Long Beach ahead, 70-66. He missed the second but Darville got the 
rebound and was fouled. He made both free throws with 10 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 "The big difference was we couldn't come up with the big rebound at the end," 
Saddleback Coach Bill Brummel said. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams were tied at 33 at the half but Saddleback, led by Jefferson, held 
the advantage early in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 He scored Saddleback's first 12 points and the Gauchos were ahead, 45-37, with 
14:55 left. Saddleback led, 55-47, with 10:02 left when Eric Ambrozich made a 
short jumper. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach then switched to a full-court press and the Gauchos started to 
struggle. Long Beach finally caught Saddleback at 61, with 4:38 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Blanton made a jumper from the free-throw line to give Long Beach a 
63-61 lead with 3:50 left. Saddleback was never tied or in the lead again. 
</P>
<P>
 Jefferson finished with 21 points and nine rebounds and Whitlock added 17 and 
Walsh 15 for Saddleback. 
</P>
</TEXT>
