<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA CORNER; FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 DEL MAR -- Got the couch-potato blues? Up and at 'em to the 1994 California 
Bike, Sport and Adventure Fair, 10 a.m.-5 p.m. Saturday to next Sunday in the 
Exhibit Hall at the Del Mar Fairgrounds, 2260 Jimmy Durante Blvd. More than 90 
booths featuring sports and health products, plus demonstrations and 
competitions. $6, general; $3, kids 6-12; free for kids under 6. The Festival 
Fun Bicycle Ride and Tandem Rally is on Sunday. (619) 595-3895. 
</P>
<P>
 BORREGO SPRINGS -- Handcrafted works by 75 artisans are showcased at the fifth 
annual Borrego Springs Crafts Faire, 9 a.m.-5 p.m. Saturday to next Sunday. The 
free show, sponsored by the Borrego Springs Chamber of Commerce, is in 
Christmas Circle, in the center of town. (619) 767-5555. While in the desert, 
check out the 18th Festival of Art and Flowers, 11 a.m.-3 p.m. next Sunday in 
the rose garden at La Casa del Zorro, 3845 Yaqui Pass Road. Sponsored by the 
Borrego Springs Arts Guild. Free. (800) 824-1884. 
</P>
<P>
 LOS OLIVOS -- Creations by women artists take the limelight for the seventh 
annual "Ladies First," a celebration in 10 galleries in the downtown area. 
Receptions, exhibits and demonstrations are about 10 a.m.-5 p.m. March 19-20. 
(805) 688-2445. 
</P>
<P>
 VENTURA -- Culture and coffee join forces at the ArtWalk and Java Jump, 5-9:30 
p.m. March 26. Seven coffeehouses and more than 20 art galleries host open 
houses along downtown's Main Street (between Ash Street and Ventura Avenue) and 
on adjacent streets. Free. A courtesy shuttle is available throughout the 
evening. (805) 658-4726. 
</P>
<P>
 PISMO BEACH -- Celebrate a coastal California Easter: Eggs are decorated, 
hunted and tossed at the free Easter Egg Hunt for kids, 10 a.m. April 2 on the 
beach just south of the Pismo Pier, and an Easter service is at 7 a.m. April 3 
on the Pismo Pier. (800) 443-7778. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
